                Note that these forms also end in <strong>-e</strong> (<em>sie</em> and
                <em>wære</em>) and <strong>-en</strong>
                (<em>sien</em> and <em>wæren</em>) like other subjunctives, and so should be easy to spot.
                It is worth learning to recognise these forms of '<em>beon</em>'
                as they are some of the most commonly encountered verbs.
            </p>
